  "body_json": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null,
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Church"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "church"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is comprised of baptized disciples joined together by the Holy Spirit who regularly meet together for doctrine, fellowship, communion, and prayer (Acts 2:42). "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Practically speaking, for a new gathering to be called a church, at least six baptized disciples are required; however, specific location, meeting frequency, and designated pastor are not—though those normally develop as an indigenous church matures in the five “selfs” (self-propagating, self-governing, self-supporting, self-theologizing, self-missionizing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "church-planting movement"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is a multiplication of indigenous churches planting churches that includes at least four streams of four spiritual generations together totaling more than 1,000 persons."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null,
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "People Group"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "people group"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is an ethnolinguistic group who perceive themselves to have a common affinity for one another based on language, culture, religion, and worldview. From the viewpoint of evangelization, it is the largest possible group within which the gospel can spread as a viable, indigenous church-planting movement without encountering barriers of understanding or acceptance. "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "unreached people group (UPG)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " has approximately 2 disciples or fewer out of 100 (≤ 2%) and lacks the capacity to establish indigenous churches without cross-cultural assistance."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Within the overarching UPG category are the following people groups in descending levels of engagement:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "attrs": {
          "start": 1,
          "type": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "attrs": {
                  "textAlign": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Under-Engaged."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " An "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "under-engaged people group"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " has approximately 1 disciple or fewer out of 100 (≤ 1%). More church planting teams are needed to increase fruitful engagement."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "attrs": {
                  "textAlign": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Frontier."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " A "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "frontier people group "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "has approximately 1 disciple or fewer out of 1,000 (≤ 0"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "1%) with no confirmed, sustained movement to Jesus. These groups are often geographically isolated with little to no access to the gospel; thus, pioneer work generally must begin with nonbelievers."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "attrs": {
                  "textAlign": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Unengaged"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ". An "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "unengaged UPG (UUPG)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " has no known believers or a tiny few (effectively 0%) and lacks the four primary levels of effective engagement:"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "bulletList",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "listItem",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "attrs": {
                          "textAlign": null
                        },
                        "content": [
                          {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Apostolic (pioneering) effort in residence"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "listItem",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "attrs": {
                          "textAlign": null
                        },
                        "content": [
                          {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Commitment to work in the local culture and heart language"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "listItem",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "attrs": {
                          "textAlign": null
                        },
                        "content": [
                          {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Commitment to long-term ministry"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "listItem",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "attrs": {
                          "textAlign": null
                        },
                        "content": [
                          {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Sowing the gospel in a manner consistent with the goal of seeing a church-planting movement emerge"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Broader engagement includes important contributing components that can be done by nonresident partners, including intercessory prayer, Bible translation, compassion/disaster ministry outreaches, media reach, mobilization efforts, leadership training, and work among diaspora."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
